  "prompt": "How easy is it to submit a question on Quora?",
  "response": "Submitting a question on Quora is quite straightforward and user-friendly. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you understand the process:\n\n1. **Create an Account or Log In**: First, you need to have a Quora account. If you don\u2019t have one, you can sign up using your email address, Google account, or Facebook account. If you already have an account, simply log in.\n\n2. **Navigate to the \"Add Question\" Section**:\n   - On the Quora homepage, you\u2019ll see a search bar at the top. Below the search bar, there\u2019s a button labeled **\"Add Question\"** or **\"Ask a Question\"**.\n   - Alternatively, you can click on the **\"Ask Question\"** button located in the sidebar or at the bottom of the page, depending on the device you\u2019re using.\n\n3. **Enter Your Question**:\n   - Clicking the \"Add Question\" button will open a new window or a pop-up where you can type in your question.\n   - Be as clear and concise as possible to improve the chances of getting relevant answers.\n\n4. **Add Topics**:\n   - After typing your question, Quora will prompt you to add relevant topics. These topics help categorize your question and make it visible to users who follow those topics.\n   - You can select from the suggested topics or type in your own. Adding multiple relevant topics can increase the visibility of your question.\n\n5. **Submit Your Question**:\n   - Once you\u2019re satisfied with your question and the topics, click the **\"Add Question\"** or **\"Ask Question\"** button to submit it.\n   - Your question will now be live on Quora, and other users can start answering it.\n\n6. **Optional**: You can also make your question anonymous by toggling the anonymous option before submitting it. This means your name won\u2019t be associated with the question.\n\n### Tips for Asking a Good Question on Quora:\n- **Be Clear and Specific**: Vague questions may not receive helpful answers. Be precise about what you\u2019re asking.\n- **Check for Duplicates**: Before submitting, search to see if your question has already been asked. Quora often suggests similar questions as you type.\n- **Be Polite and Respectful**: Good etiquette increases the likelihood of getting thoughtful responses.\n\nOverall, Quora\u2019s interface is designed to make the process of asking questions quick and easy, even for new users.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
